Śhrī Mātājī: Ah, not for my lectures [UNCLEAR]. I wanted these names to be a little bit announced, so that they aren’t any faint sound.

12:41 Can you hear Me now?

13:21 Today is an important date, I thought that; because it’s called as the Akshay Tritiya; Akshay means which cannot be perished, and Tritiya means the third day of the moon. That day is regarded as the most important auspicious date – we call it as Muhurta in Sanskrit, which means very suitable time, very apt time for doing something. Specially this one is the one when whatever you desire, whatever you establish, whatever you start, anything, becomes successful, it is said. And it is you know that the whole cosmos, the whole universe is under the influence or complete control of God. And He organizes Himself. So, also if He has organized the date for us which is discovered by some people, it has some meaning and one should try to pay little attention to that. That doesn’t mean that you should become a slave of astrology or anything because now you are in contact with God so you don’t have to worry about what is the date, what is... everything works out. But if you could take the help also of a date, it would be something very helpful; and that surprisingly has come on the 5th of May, the day Sahasrara was opened. So, it’s a very important date and I thought that we could have a havana where the names of Goddess, which are all mantras and which create a power; by that power, anything can be achieved. 

So, it was arranged, and it is most unexpected that so many of you have come, and it’s very, really gratifying to see all of you here. And also the way it has been arranged so spontaneously, we can see how Sahaja Yoga helps. Only I feel that somebody should try to be quiet, on the Nirvichara, so your memory works, like mine works with that. And with my memory I know where and what is kept, what is there; I might have kept in a vault 30 years back somewhere something, and I never lost it. So, I think that we should try to practice Nirvichara, absolutely in Thoughtless Awareness and Emptiness, then only things work out; when we become empty, everything works out. Our memory grows and we get what we have to achieve in our spiritual life, because we can only grow when we are empty. So, when we are doing these mantras and all that, one should try to be in Thoughtless Awareness. It would be very helpful to all of us.

So, I want to give my lecture now for Sahasrara Day. Let us all of us all of them welcoming, but I hope that you will today meditate with the idea that you are yourself very powerful and you can generate power by saying these mantras from your heart, from your full will, complete will; because we have to spread the will of God and this is how we can do it. May God bless you.

To organize it, you have to get all these [UNCLEAR] around.

